      "description": "Offering a superlative 997.2 Carrera S, a definitive example of naturally aspirated precision. This specimen features the 3.8L Direct Fuel Injection (DFI) flat-six, mated to a short-throw 6-speed manual transaxle for pure mechanical engagement. The chassis is equipped with Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM) and a limited-slip differential, ensuring exceptional lateral stability and turn-in response. A recent DME readout confirms a pristine rev history with no over-revs in higher stages. The underside is immaculate, with no oxidation on the aluminum subframes or heat-shielding. From the factory-spec torque curve to the zero-play bushings, every mechanical interface remains in showroom-fresh state. This is a benchmark-tier 911 for the technical purist.",
